<task id="R7-084" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>Implement typed config forms for 5 priority executors (FR-23)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <wave>8</wave>
    <estimated-effort>4-5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>code-page, ui, wave-8</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>083 (renderer wired)</dependencies>
    <fr-coverage>FR-23 (priority schemas)</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement rich typed config forms for the 5 priority executors per spec FR-16/FR-23:
    AI Analysis, AI Completion (built in Wave 1), Condition, EntityNameValidator (sibling pattern),
    CreateNotification. Each form: text inputs, dropdowns, JSON sub-editors as needed; validates
    input against schema. These 5 are the proof-of-concept that the schema-driven renderer
    (task 083) produces usable forms for real-world authoring scenarios.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React + Fluent UI v9 developer. Comfortable iterating on schema-driven UI to match
    hand-crafted form quality. Familiar with the 5 specific executors' config shapes.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Rich `ExecutorConfigSchema` definitions returned by the BFF `GetConfigSchema()` method on
    these 5 executors (work happens BFF-side in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/`):
    1. `AiAnalysisNodeExecutor.GetConfigSchema()` — fields: documentScope, toolBindings (JSON), temperature (number), promptOverride (JSON sub-editor)
    2. `AiCompletionNodeExecutor.GetConfigSchema()` — fields: temperature (number 0-2), maxOutputTokens (number), promptOverride (JSON sub-editor)
    3. `ConditionNodeExecutor.GetConfigSchema()` — fields: expression (string), trueBranch (string), falseBranch (string)
    4. `EntityNameValidatorNodeExecutor.GetConfigSchema()` — fields: entitySetName (string), uniqueCheck (boolean), maxLength (number)
    5. `CreateNotificationNodeExecutor.GetConfigSchema()` — fields: recipientType (enum), template (string), priority (enum)

    After BFF schemas are populated, the canvas `TypedConfigForm.tsx` (task 083) automatically renders
    the 5 forms with full field-typed inputs. No new canvas-side files needed — just verify rendering.
    Add canvas-side __tests__ for the 5 specific forms (Vitest + RTL).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="ai-analysis-executor">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiAnalysisNodeExecutor.cs</file>
