  <context>
    <background>
      Spec FR-16 requires every executor to declare a config schema via `GetConfigSchema()`. Task 032
      (Wave 3) added the method to all 33 executors with placeholder schemas. This task fleshes out the
      5 priority executor schemas with real fields, defaults, descriptions, required-flags. The canvas
      renderer (task 083) consumes these schemas automatically — no canvas-side rendering work needed,
      only schema-DTO authoring on BFF side and tests on canvas side.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="083" status="prerequisite">Schema-driven renderer must exist before its schemas are useful.</dependency>
      <dependency task="032" status="prerequisite">Wave 3 task 032 added placeholder schemas — this task replaces placeholders with rich content for the 5 priority executors.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 085 fills out remaining 28 executor schemas (placeholder forms OK).</item>
      <item>Task 089b runs UI tests against these 5 forms in the browser.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL · 📋 REASON: BFF code-impl + canvas tests, ADR-006+021+029+038 applicable, quality gates Step 9.5 required · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-23 + Wave 3 task 030 design notes + AiCompletionForm.tsx (hand-crafted reference).
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Verify W3 task 033 deployed">
      Confirm BFF endpoint deployed. If not, STOP.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Author rich schema for AiAnalysisNodeExecutor.GetConfigSchema()">
      Replace placeholder schema with: `documentScope` (string, required), `toolBindings` (json), `temperature` (number, default 0.7, min 0, max 2), `promptOverride` (json, optional). Field descriptions reference Action's prompt template.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Author rich schema for AiCompletionNodeExecutor.GetConfigSchema()">
      Fields: `temperature` (number 0-2, default 0.7), `maxOutputTokens` (number, default 4096), `promptOverride` (json, optional). NOTE: AiCompletion does NOT take Tool or Document per FR-13.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Author rich schema for ConditionNodeExecutor.GetConfigSchema()">
      Fields: `expression` (string, required, description "JavaScript-like condition expression"), `trueBranch` (string, required), `falseBranch` (string, required).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Author rich schema for EntityNameValidatorNodeExecutor.GetConfigSchema()">
      Fields: `entitySetName` (string, required), `uniqueCheck` (boolean, default true), `maxLength` (number, default 100).
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Author rich schema for CreateNotificationNodeExecutor.GetConfigSchema()">
      Fields: `recipientType` (enum: user/team/contact, required), `template` (string, required), `priority` (enum: low/normal/high, default normal).
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Build BFF + canvas">
      `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` + `cd src/client/code-pages/PlaybookBuilder && npm run build:prod`.
      Both: 0 errors, 0 new warnings.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Add canvas-side Vitest tests">
      Create `src/client/code-pages/PlaybookBuilder/src/components/properties/__tests__/TypedConfigForm.test.tsx` with tests for:
      - Renders all 5 priority executor schemas without errors
      - Required-field marker shows for required fields
      - Validation error fires on empty required field
      - JSON sub-editor validates JSON syntax
      Mock the schema fetch (do NOT mock HttpMessageHandler — direct schema injection).
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `/code-review` on the 5 modified BFF executors + new test file.
      Run `/adr-check` against ADR-006 + ADR-021 + ADR-029 + ADR-038.
      Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish-task084/` — measure publish size, report delta vs baseline. Expect minimal (each schema is ~30 LOC).
      Run `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` — confirm no new HIGH-severity CVE.
      Fix findings.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 084 status complete; advance to next Wave 8 task.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Commit">
      Commit message:
      `feat(bff+playbookbuilder/r7): typed config schemas + form tests for 5 priority executors (Wave 8 task 084, FR-23)`. No PR yet.
    </step>
  </steps>

